CReVB6NL\",\"type\":\"tool_result\",\"content\":\"     1→---\\n     2→description: \\\"Assess a new agent's hook/lifecycle compatibility with the Entire CLI\\\"\\n     3→---\\n     4→\\n     5→# Research Command\\n     6→\\n     7→Assess whether a target AI coding agent's hook/lifecycle model is compatible with the Entire CLI before writing any Go code.\\n     8→\\n     9→## Parameters\\n    10→\\n    11→Collect these before proceeding (ask the user if not provided):\\n    12→\\n    13→| Parameter | Example | Description |\\n    14→|-----------|---------|-------------|\\n    15→| `AGENT_NAME` | \\\"Windsurf\\\" | Human-readable agent name |\\n    16→| `AGENT_SLUG` | \\\"windsurf\\\" | Lowercase slug for file/directory paths |\\n    17→| `AGENT_BIN` | \\\"windsurf\\\" | CLI binary name |\\n    18→| `LIVE_COMMAND` | \\\"windsurf --project .\\\" | Full command to launch agent |\\n    19→| `EVENTS_OR_UNKNOWN` | \\\"unknown\\\" | Known hook event names, or \\\"unknown\\\" |\\n    20→\\n    21→## Architecture References\\n    22→\\n    23→Read these to understand the Entire lifecycle model:\\n    24→\\n    25→- **Implementation guide**: `docs/architecture/agent-guide.md`\\n    26→- **Integration checklist**: `docs/architecture/agent-integration-checklist.md`\\n    27→\\n    28→## Procedure\\n    29→\\n    30→### Phase 1: Architecture Inspection\\n    31→\\n    32→Read these repo files to understand the Entire lifecycle model that the agent must integrate with:\\n    33→\\n    34→**Required reading:**\\n    35→\\n    36→1. `cmd/entire/cli/agent/agent.go` — Read to find the `Agent` interface and all optional capability interfaces\\n    37→2. `cmd/entire/cli/agent/event.go` — Read to find all `EventType` constants (the normalized lifecycle events agents must map to)\\n    38→3. `cmd/entire/cli/hook_registry.go` — How native hook names are registered and routed\\n    39→4. `cmd/entire/cli/lifecycle.go` — `DispatchLifecycleEvent` handler\\n    40→5. `docs/architecture/agent-guide.md` — Full implementation guide\\n    41→6. `docs/architecture/agent-integration-checklist.md` — Validation criteria\\n    42→\\n    43→**Reference implementations:** Run `Glob(\\\"cmd/entire/cli/agent/*/\\\")` to discover all existing agent packages. Pick 1-2 as reference. In each, focus on `lifecycle.go` (ParseHookEvent), `hooks.go` (HookSupport), and `types.go` (hook input structs).\\n    44→\\n    45→### Phase 2: Static Capability Checks\\n    46→\\n    47→Non-destructive CLI probing. Record PASS/WARN/FAIL for each:\\n    48→\\n    49→| Check | Command | PASS | FAIL |\\n    50→|-------|---------|------|------|\\n    51→| Binary present | `command -v $AGENT_BIN` | Found | Not found (blocker) |\\n    52→| Help output | `$AGENT_BIN --help` or `$AGENT_BIN help` | Available | No help |\\n    53→| Version info | `$AGENT_BIN --version` or `$AGENT_BIN version` | Available | N/A |\\n    54→| Hook keywords | Scan help for: hook, lifecycle, callback, event, trigger, pre-, post-, plugin, extension | Found | None found |\\n    55→| Session keywords | Scan help for: session, resume, continue, history, transcript, context | Found | None found |\\n    56→| Config directory | Check `~/.$AGENT_SLUG/`, `~/.config/$AGENT_SLUG/`, `./$AGENT_SLUG/`, `./.${AGENT_SLUG}/` | Found | None found |\\n    57→| Documentation | Web search for hook/plugin/extension docs | Found | None found |\\n    58→\\n    59→### Phase 3: Test Script Creation\\n    60→\\n    61→Based on Phase 2 findings, create an **agent-specific** test script:\\n    62→\\n    63→```\\n    64→scripts/test-$AGENT_SLUG-agent-integration.sh\\n    65→```\\n    66→\\n    67→The script is tailored to the specific agent's hook mechanism (not a generic template). Adapt the hook wiring section based on what Phase 2 discovered.\\n    68→\\n    69→**Script structure:**\\n    70→\\n    71→```bash\\n    72→#!/usr/bin/env bash\\n    73→set -euo pipefail\\n    74→\\n    75→AGENT_NAME=\\\"...\\\"\\n    76→AGENT_SLUG=\\\"...\\\"\\n    77→AGENT_BIN=\\\"...\\\"\\n    78→PROBE_DIR=\\\".entire/tmp/probe-${AGENT_SLUG}-$(date +%s)\\\"\\n    79→```\\n    80→\\n    81→**Required sections:**\\n    82→\\n    83→1. **Static checks** — Re-runnable binary/version/help checks\\n    84→2. **Hook wiring** — Create workspace-local config that intercepts hooks and dumps stdin JSON to `$PROBE_DIR/captures/<event-name>-<timestamp>.json`\\n    85→3. **Run modes:**\\n    86→   - `--run-cmd '<cmd>'` — Automated: launch agent, wait, collect\\n    87→   - `--manual-live` — Interactive: user runs agent manually, presses Enter\\n    88→4. **Capture collection** — List and pretty-print all payload files\\n    89→5. **Cleanup** — Restore original config (unless `--keep-config`)\\n    90→6. **Verdict** — PASS/WARN/FAIL per lifecycle event + COMPATIBLE/PARTIAL/INCOMPATIBLE\\n    91→\\n    92→### Phase 4: Execution & Analysis\\n    93→\\n    94→Run the script and analyze:\\n    95→\\n    96→1. **Execute**: `chmod +x scripts/test-$AGENT_SLUG-agent-integration.sh && scripts/test-$AGENT_SLUG-agent-integration.sh --manual-live`\\n    97→2. **For each captured payload**: show command, artifact path, decoded JSON\\n    98→3. **Lifecycle mapping**: native hook name -> Entire EventType\\n    99→4. **Field coverage**: which `Event` struct fields can be populated per event\\n   100→\\n   101→### Phase 5: Compatibility Report\\n   102→\\n   103→Generate structured markdown output directly to the user:\\n   104→\\n   105→```markdown\\n   106→# Agent Compatibility Report: $AGENT_NAME\\n   107→\\n   108→**Date:** YYYY-MM-DD\\n   109→**Agent:** $AGENT_NAME v$VERSION\\n   110→**Binary:** $AGENT_BIN\\n   111→**Verdict:** COMPATIBLE / PARTIAL / INCOMPATIBLE\\n   112→\\n   113→## Static Capability Checks\\n   114→\\n   115→| Check | Result | Notes |\\n   116→|-------|--------|-------|\\n   117→| Binary present | PASS/FAIL | path |\\n   118→| Help available | PASS/FAIL | |\\n   119→| Hook keywords found | PASS/WARN/FAIL | keywords found |\\n   120→| 