\\n     7→Generate the E2E test suite for a new agent integration. Uses the research report's findings and the existing E2E test infrastructure.\\n     8→\\n     9→## Parameters\\n    10→\\n    11→Collect these before proceeding (ask the user if not provided):\\n    12→\\n    13→| Parameter | Example | Description |\\n    14→|-----------|---------|-------------|\\n    15→| `AGENT_NAME` | \\\"Windsurf\\\" | Human-readable agent name |\\n    16→| `AGENT_SLUG` | \\\"windsurf\\\" | Lowercase slug for file/directory paths |\\n    17→| `AGENT_BIN` | \\\"windsurf\\\" | CLI binary name |\\n    18→| `LIVE_COMMAND` | \\\"windsurf --project .\\\" | Full command to launch agent |\\n    19→| `EVENTS_OR_UNKNOWN` | \\\"unknown\\\" | Known hook event names, or \\\"unknown\\\" |\\n    20→\\n    21→## Prerequisites\\n    22→\\n    23→- The research command should have been run first (or equivalent knowledge of the agent's hook model)\\n    24→- If no research report exists, ask the user about the agent's hook events, transcript format, and config mechanism\\n    25→\\n    26→## Architecture References\\n    27→\\n    28→- **Implementation guide**: `docs/architecture/agent-guide.md`\\n    29→- **Integration checklist**: `docs/architecture/agent-integration-checklist.md`\\n    30→\\n    31→## Procedure\\n    32→\\n    33→### Step 1: Read E2E Test Infrastructure\\n    34→\\n    35→Read these files to understand the existing test patterns:\\n    36→\\n    37→1. `e2e/tests/main_test.go` — `TestMain` builds the CLI binary (via `entire.BinPath()`), runs preflight checks for required binaries (git, tmux, agent CLIs), sets up artifact directories, and configures env\\n    38→2. `e2e/testutil/repo.go` — `RepoState` struct (holds agent, dir, artifact dir, head/checkpoint refs), `SetupRepo` (creates temp git repo, runs `entire enable`, patches settings), `ForEachAgent` (runs a test per registered agent with repo setup, concurrency gating, and timeout scaling)\\n    39→3. `e2e/agents/agent.go` — `Agent` interface (`Name`, `Binary`, `EntireAgent`, `PromptPattern`, `TimeoutMultiplier`, `RunPrompt`, `StartSession`, `Bootstrap`, `IsTransientError`), `Register()` for agent self-registration in `init()`, `RegisterGate()` for concurrency limits, `AcquireSlot`/`ReleaseSlot` for gating\\n    40→4. `e2e/agents/tmux.go` — `TmuxSession` for interactive PTY-based tests: `NewTmuxSession`, `Send`, `SendKeys`, `WaitFor` (with settle-time logic), `Capture`, `Close`\\n    41→5. `e2e/testutil/assertions.go` — Rich assertion helpers: `AssertFileExists`, `WaitForFileExists`, `AssertNewCommits`, `WaitForCheckpoint`, `AssertCheckpointAdvanced`, `AssertHasCheckpointTrailer`, `AssertCheckpointExists`, `AssertCommitLinkedToCheckpoint`, `AssertCheckpointMetadataComplete`, `ValidateCheckpointDeep`, and many more\\n    42→6. `e2e/testutil/metadata.go` — `CheckpointMetadata`, `SessionMetadata`, `TokenUsage`, `Attribution`, `SessionRef` types; `CheckpointPath()` helper for sharded directory layout\\n    43→7. `e2e/entire/entire.go` — CLI wrapper: `BinPath()` (builds from source or uses `E2E_ENTIRE_BIN`), `Enable`, `Disable`, `RewindList`, `Rewind`, `RewindLogsOnly`, `Explain`, `ExplainGenerate`, `ExplainCommit`, `Resume`\\n    44→8. `e2e/testutil/artifacts.go` — Automatic artifact capture via `t.Cleanup`: `CaptureArtifacts` saves git-log, git-tree, checkpoint metadata, entire logs, and tmux pane content\\n    45→\\n    46→### Step 2: Read Existing E2E Test Scenarios\\n    47→\\n    48→Run `Glob(\\\"e2e/tests/*_test.go\\\")` to find all existing test files. Read a few to understand the patterns:\\n    49→- How tests use `testutil.ForEachAgent` with a timeout and callback `func(t, s, ctx)`\\n    50→- How prompts are written inline (no separate prompt template file)\\n    51→- How `s.RunPrompt`, `s.Git`, `s.StartSession`, `s.WaitFor`, `s.Send` are used\\n    52→- How assertions validate checkpoints, rewind, metadata, etc.\\n    53→\\n    54→### Step 3: Read Checkpoint Scenarios Doc\\n    55