leSessionManualCommit\\n   238→   ```\\n   239→4. **Add mise task**: Remind the user to add a `test:e2e:${agent_slug}` task in `mise.toml` and update CI workflows\\n   240→\\n   241→## Key Conventions\\n   242→\\n   243→- **Build tag**: All E2E test files must have `//go:build e2e` as the first line\\n   244→- **Package**: `package tests` for test files in `e2e/tests/`; `package agents` for agent implementations in `e2e/agents/`\\n   245→- **Parallel**: `ForEachAgent` handles parallelism — do not call `t.Parallel()` inside the callback\\n   246→- **Repo setup**: `ForEachAgent` calls `SetupRepo` automatically — do not call it manually\\n   247→- **Prompts**: Write prompts inline in the test. Include \\\"Do not ask for confirmation\\\" to prevent agent stalling\\n   248→- **Assertions**: Use helpers from `e2e/testutil/assertions.go` — see `AssertFileExists`, `WaitForCheckpoint`, `AssertCommitLinkedToCheckpoint`, `ValidateCheckpointDeep`, etc.\\n   249→- **CLI operations**: Use the `e2e/entire` package (`entire.Enable`, `entire.RewindList`, `entire.Rewind`, etc.) — never call the binary via raw `exec.Command`\\n   250→- **No hardcoded paths**: Use `s.Dir` for repo paths, `s.ArtifactDir` for artifacts\\n   251→- **Console logging**: All operations through `s.RunPrompt`, `s.Git`, `s.Send`, `s.WaitFor` are automatically logged to `console.log`\\n   252→- **Transient errors**: `s.RunPrompt` auto-retries once on transient API errors via `IsTransientError`\\n   253→- **Interactive tests**: Use `s.StartSession`, `s.Send`, `s.WaitFor` — tmux pane is auto-captured in artifacts\\n   254→- **Run commands**: `mise run test:e2e:${slug} TestName` — see `e2e/README.md` for all options\\n   255→- **Do NOT run E2E tests**: They make real API calls. Only write the code and print commands.\\n   256→\\n   257→## Output\\n   258→\\n   259→Summarize what was created/modified:\\n   260→- Files added or modified\\n   261→- New agent implementation details (how it invokes the agent, auth setup